# .streamlit/secrets.toml.example
#
# Note: The NIFTY 50 Latent Market Regime Discovery & Risk Intelligence Platform
# operates entirely on public datasets (yfinance) and local parquet feature matrices.
# No secrets, databases, or third-party API keys are required to boot the application.
#
# If you plan to deploy this on Streamlit Community Cloud, you can leave the "Secrets"
# configuration completely blank during the setup steps.
#
# This file is provided purely as a standard reference for deployment configuration.
